FirstReport

OVERALL ANALYSIS

PAYED IN FULL VERSUS OF ALL OF THE REST FOR OVERALL DATA

Conclusion : The people who payed full is 44% and the rest of people different from the onews who payed full is 56%

train=read.csv('/home/gingasu/Downloads/report_20180906_1235PM.csv',
               header=T , sep=",")
 

full=train[train["Loan.Status"]=='Paid in Full',]
NotFull=train[train["Loan.Status"]!='Paid in Full',]
sizef=dim(full)[1]
sizenf=dim(NotFull)[1]
all=c(sizef, sizenf)
barplot(all,main="Pail In  full Versus Rest",ylab="Quantity",col=c("red","blue"),ylim=c(0,sizenf+100),legend = c("Payed Full " , "The Rest"),args.legend = list(title = "Legend: Color~Year", x = "topleft", cex = .7))
points(all,lw=2,col="black")
text(1,sizef+110,sizef,cex=0.7)
text(2,sizenf+50,sizenf,cex=0.7)

PAID ANALYSIS OVERALL

Conclusion : Paid in Full and Paid in full NSF1 have the largest occurences , the other types of paied types are pretty smaller

train=read.csv('/home/gingasu/Downloads/report_20180906_1235PM.csv',
               header=T , sep=",")
 
train[,'Loan.Status']=sapply(train[,"Loan.Status"],as.character)

written=train[grepl("Paid",train[,'Loan.Status']),]

labels=unique(written$Loan.Status)

good_label=c()
good_size=c()
for (l in labels) {
  nr=dim(train[train["Loan.Status"]==l,])[1]
  if (nr>1)
  {
    good_label=c(good_label,l)
    good_size=c(good_size,nr)
  }
  
  
}


barplot(good_size,main="Loan  default PAIED",ylab="Quantity",
        ylim=c(0,100),legend = good_label,col=rainbow(14),
        args.legend = list(title = "Legend", x = "topright", cex = .6))

WRITTEN ANALYS OVERALL

Conclusion : Written off NSF1 , Centrallized Collections , Collection Agency has the large proportion , smaller proportions for ,, writen off NSF6 , written off NSF , written off nsf 5 , also written of NSF1 Bankruptcy

train[,'Loan.Status']=sapply(train[,"Loan.Status"],as.character)

written=train[grepl("Written",train[,'Loan.Status']),]

labels=unique(written$Loan.Status)
  
good_label=c()
good_size=c()
for (l in labels) {
  nr=dim(train[train["Loan.Status"]==l,])[1]
  if (nr>10)
  {
    good_label=c(good_label,l)
    good_size=c(good_size,nr)
  }
 
   
}


barplot(good_size,main="Loan  default Written",ylab="Quantity",
       ylim=c(0,100),legend = good_label,col=rainbow(16),
        args.legend = list(title = "Legend", x = "topright", cex = .5))

200 DOLLAR ANALYSIS

train[,"Loan.Amount"]=sapply(train[,"Loan.Amount"],as.character)
values=c()
for   (row in  (1:dim(train)[1]))
  
{
  
  val=as.numeric(gsub("[^\\d]+", "", train[row,"Loan.Amount"], perl=TRUE))/100
  values=c(values,val)
}

train["values"]=values

tr200=train[train['values']<=200,]

library(plotrix)
total_dim=dim(tr200)[1]
paied=tr200[grepl("Paid",tr200[,'Loan.Status']),]
dim_paied=dim(paied)[1]

# extracting  written

written=tr200[grepl("Written",tr200[,'Loan.Status']),]
dim_written=dim(written)[1]

# extracting past 
past=tr200[grepl("Past",tr200[,'Loan.Status']),]
dim_past=dim(past)[1]

#
neiCoal=c(dim_paied, dim_written, dim_past)
slices=neiCoal
percent= round(slices/sum(slices)*100)

lb = c("Loans Paied","Loans Written","Loans that  Past")
lb=paste(lb,percent)
lb=paste(lb,"%",sep=" ")

pie3D(slices,labels = lb, col=rainbow(length(lb)),explode=0.08,
      main="Performance of 0-200$ Loans")

#Distribution by Loan Value

n200=dim(tr200)[1]
n300=dim(tr300)[1]
n400=dim(tr400)[1]
n500=dim(tr500)[1]
n600=dim(tr600)[1]
n700=dim(tr700)[1]
n800=dim(tr800)[1]
s=c(n200,n300,n400,n500,n600,n700,n800)
label=c('0-200','200-300','300-400','400-500','500-600','600-700','>700')
barplot(s,main="Number of LOANS by AMMOUNT OF MONEY",ylab="No of Loans",
        ylim=c(0,sum(s)+1000),legend = label,col=rainbow(7),
        args.legend = list(title = "Legend", x = "topright", cex = .7))
points(s,lw=2,col="black")
text(1,n200+100,n200,cex=0.7)
text(2,n300+100,n300,cex=0.7)
text(3,n400+100,n400,cex=0.7)
text(4,n500+100,n500,cex=0.7)
text(5,n600+100,n600,cex=0.7)
text(6,n700+100,n700,cex=0.7)
text(7,n800+100,n800,cex=0.7)

200$ BREAKDOWN

written=tr200[grepl("Written",tr200[,'Loan.Status']),]

labels=unique(written$Loan.Status)
 
good_label=c()
good_size=c()
for (l in labels) {
  nr=dim(train[train["Loan.Status"]==l,])[1]
  if (nr>3)
  {
    good_label=c(good_label,l)
    good_size=c(good_size,nr)
  }
 
   
}

barplot(good_size,main="BREAKDOWN  200",ylab="Quantity",
       ylim=c(0,200),legend = good_label,col=rainbow(14),
        args.legend = list(title = "Legend: Color~Year", x = "topright", cex = .5))
